history.content: Hi! EECS 16A TA here. We will not be allowing time-conflicts with lecture. We encourage students who can attend live lecture to do so unless they are in a time zone that puts the class at an odd hour. In addition, we will not be providing alternate exams due to exam/time conflicts. Hope this helps in making a decision!

Are we allowed to take classes that directly conflict with EECS16A Lectures? It won't let me in from the waitlist because I can't enroll in the class because it conflicts with a class I have. Since classes are online and recorded, this shouldn't be an issue?
history.subject: EECS16A Conflicting Time Lecture?
